Name: Arthur Church ( F )
Notes: University Reader in Botany ( 1910-1930 ) , elected a Fellow of the Royal Society in 1921

Name: Francis Cole
Notes: Professor of Zoology at Reading University ( 1906-1939 ) , founder of the Cole Museum of Zoology

Name: Hugh Davies
Notes: Welsh clergyman and botanist , whose main work , Welsh Botanology ( 1813 ) , was the first to cross-reference the names of plants in Welsh with their scientific names

Name: William Weekes Fowler
Notes: Matriculated at New College before transferring to Jesus with a scholarship ; a clergyman , headmaster and entomologist who was President of the Incorporated Association of Head Masters and President of the Entomological Society of London

Notes: Professor of zoology and comparative anatomy at Trinity College , Dublin

Name: Edward Lhuyd
Notes: Naturalist , botanist , linguist , geographer and antiquary

Name: Robert Cyril Layton Perkins
Notes: Entomologist , noted for his work on the fauna of the islands of Hawaii

Name: Edward Bagnall Poulton ( F )
Notes: Appointed Hope Professor of Zoology in 1893

Name: Ronald Winckworth
Notes: Natural historian , President of the Conchological Society of Great Britain and Ireland and Vice-President of the Linnean Society
